at products and readytoeat products and prepared foods consisting of precooked entrees and bacon the  smithfield foods inc together with its subsidiaries produces and markets various fresh meat and packaged meats products in the united states and internationally it operates through five segments fresh pork packaged meats hog production international and corporate the company offers fresh pork products such as butts loins picnics and ribs as well as leaners hogs and beef and poultry products it also produces packaged meats including smoked and boiled hams bacon sausage hot dogs deli canned meats and luncheon meats specialty products comprising pepperoni dry meat products and readytoeat products and prepared foods consisting of precooked entrees and bacon the company markets its products to supermarket chains wholesale distributors the foodservice industry including fast food restaurant and hotel chains hospitals and other institutional customers export markets and other further processors smithfield foods sells its products through salespersons and independent commission brokers the company was founded in  and is headquartered in smithfield virginia as of september   smithfield foods inc operates as a subsidiary of henan luohe shuanghui industry group limited liability company detailed description  commerce streetsmithfield va united statesfounded in  employees phone  wwwsmithfieldfoodscom key executives for smithfield foods inc mr kenneth marc sullivan chief executive officer president and director age  mr glenn t nunziata chief financial officer and executive vice president age  mr joseph b sebring president of packaged meats division age  mr dariusz nowakowski president of smithfield europe age  mr dennis h treacy president of the smithfield foundation age  compensation as of fiscal year  smithfield foods inc key developments smithfield foods inc introduces new innovative venture smithfield bioscience apr   smithfield foods inc announced the launch of smithfield bioscience a new strategic platform within the organization that leverages byproducts from the meat production process for the development of pharmaceuticals nutraceuticals and medical device solutions smithfield is taking a leadership position in developing these types of cutting edge initiatives which support a range of biotechnology solutions in areas of human therapeutics tissue fabrication and regenerative medicine smithfield sells byproducts to pharmaceutical and nutraceutical companies who use these materials to develop drugs that treat a range of issues from indigestion to hypothyroidism to deep vein thrombosis smithfield bioscience will expand upon these efforts by exploring new methods and technologies for addressing concerns such as tissue regeneration and the availability of viable human organs for transplantation this dedicated team is solely focused on the responsible and transparent pursuit of these sciencebased endeavors one of smithfield biosciences first projects is the participation in the advanced regenerative manufacturing institute armi a publicprivate us manufacturing initiative that brings together  organizations across academia advanced robotics and pharmaceutical to develop nextgeneration technologies and manufacturing processes for cells tissue and organ development with funding from the department of defense the consortium is initially focused on technologies that would enable the repair and replacement of human tissue of soldiers injured in combat smithfield bioscience is also working with harvard medical school and columbia university on the research and development of immunology therapies smithfield foods reports earnings results for the full year  mar   smithfield foods reported earnings results for the full year  for the full year the companys net income increased  to  million operating profit was up  to  million and ebitda increased  to  billion total sales were  billion which are relatively unchanged from  capex was approximately  m