to antibiotics use in farm animals providing a practical explanation to consumers and customers that offers greater clarity it said the efforts were driven by an internal antibiotics task force “which supports smithfields commitment to industryleading antibiotics initiatives” the company stated this new line from pure farms reflects smithfields continued commitment to meeting the needs of all consumers with good food that is made the right way said stewart leeth vice president of regulatory affairs and chief sustainability officer for smithfield foods in the company’s news release this commitment led to the creation of this new line and other bold steps we continue to take to ensure our products exceed our customers and consumers expectations no comments log in to comment add new comment if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form if youre a human dont change the following field enter your name your first name please enable javascript to use this form your name subject comment  more information about text formatsplain textno html tags allowedlines and paragraphs break automatically leave this field blank   trending company news afiathe maschhoffslarson electronics six business plan tips bargain buying strengthens cme live cattle futures pork industry backs epa request to delay emissions reporting requirements saving taxpayers more than  billion forum will address livestock id standards and technology custom burgers  drinks boost mcdonalds sales shares jump farm stress a fivestep approach to alleviating stress cme live cattle turn higher on futures cash discount not necessarily better – just different  copyright  farm journal inc all rights reserved   w th terr suite  lenexa ks  welcome to our redesigned homepage scroll down for more stories smithfield foods inc execut